title: TV tonight: 'Vampire Diaries,' 'Billy'
text:
USA TODAY's Robert Bianco previews the television lineup for Thursday, October 8. VPC
Damon (Ian Somerhalder) must go on without the love of his life as 'The Vampire Diaries' returns for a new season. (Photo: Bob Mahoney, CW)
6 CONNECT 56 TWEET LINKEDIN 1 COMMENT EMAIL MORE The Vampire Diaries/The Originals
CW, 8 ET/PT
CW's two blood-sucker dramas — the original Diaries and its Originals spin-off — return. On Diaries , Damon must learn to live (well, sort of live) without Elena, now that she's in a coma and the actress who played her, Nina Dobrev, is off the show. Then on Originals , the brothers deal with new threats and old divisions.
USA TODAY
Critic's Corner chat: Mon., 2 p.m. ET
How to Get Away With Murder
ABC, 10 ET/PT
Resetting a series, which is what Murder has to do, is never easy, and we're only two weeks into the season, so there's obviously no reason to panic. That said, though, it hasn't been a particularly enchanting two weeks. We know not to demand sense from the show's courtroom antics, but we should be able to expect better than a plot hinging on evidence attorneys blithely accept from a stranger in a bathroom. And while we'd watch the fabulous Viola Davis do anything, that doesn't mean we want to watch her weep every week.Consider that an early warning.
Billy Eichner returns to TruTV with 'Billy on the Street.' (Photo: TruTV)
Billy on the Street
TruTV, 10:30 ET/PT
Billy Eichner's series opens its TruTV stint with an endearingly amusing performance from Tina Fey, whose "Latina Fey" game is an ingenious highpoint. The other segments are hit and miss — Eichner is funnier when he's faking anger than when he's faking geniality — but Fey makes up for any lapses.
